        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        Vt ameris, amabilis esto.
                        An fortuna in nostra potestate?
                    </marginalia_text>
                    <X-ref book_title="Ars amatoria" language="LA" person="Ovid" text=" Vt ameris, amabilis esto"/> <!--2: 107-->
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>
                "Be lovely, so that you may be loved." Whether fortune is in our power?
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
        <marginalia hand="Italian">
            <language ident="LA">
                <position book_orientation="0" place="tail">
                    <marginalia_text>
                        An vt Ars causa Virtutis; sic virtus, Fortuna[e]? Fortuna, Foelicitatis?
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>
                Whether, as art is the cause of virtue, thus virtue is the cause of fortune? Whether fortune is the cause of hapiness? 
            </translation>
